com.interpss.algo.subAreaNet

Interface SubAreaNetProcessor<TBus,TBra,TSub,TState>

  • Type Parameters:
    TBus - Bus object generic type
    TBra - Branch object generic type
    TSub - SubArea/Network generic type
    TState - Network state (current, voltage) generic type, for example, Complex for single phase analysis
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseSubAreaNetProcessorImpl, SubAreaAcscProcessorImpl, SubAreaPosProcessorImpl, SubNetworkAcscProcessorImpl, SubNetworkPosProcessorImpl

    public interface SubAreaNetProcessor<TBus,TBra,TSub,TState>
    Interface for SubArea or SubNetwork processing. It begins by defining a set of cutting branches. It finds SubAreas in the network and SubArea interface buses.
    (1) It starts from a parent/main network. Through the processing, a set of SubArea/Networks are defined by the SubAreaFlag values. (2) If it is SubNetwork processing, it builds SubNetworks based on the SubArea info. Before the SubNetwork processing, all buses/branches in SubArea are contained by the parent (main) network (Bus/Branch.network = Parent Network). After the SubNetwork processing, buses/branches in SubNetwork are contained by the SubNetwork (Bus/Branch.network = SubNetwork), although the parent network still holds reference to all the buses and branches.

      • processSubAreaNet

        java.util.List<TSub> processSubAreaNet()
                                throws InterpssException
        Process SubArea by automatically group buses into SubAreas based on the defined cutting branches set. If it is SubNetwork processing, SubNetwork and the parent Network object relationship will be created. The cutting branches are turn-off after the processing.
        Returns:
        the SubArea/Network list
        Throws:
        InterpssException

      • processSubAreaNet

        java.util.List<TSub> processSubAreaNet(boolean singleSide)
                                throws InterpssException
        Same processing logic as the processSubAreaNet() method. If SingleSide = true, only process the SubArea side of the network. The SubArea location as follows: When CuttingBranch.splitSide = FromSide fromBus toBus | --- CutBranch ---- | [SubArea] When CuttingBranch.splitSide = ToSide fromBus toBus | --- CutBranch ---- | [SubArea] The cutting branches are turn-off after the processing.
        Parameters:
        sigleSide - flag for controlling only process the SubArea side of the network
        Returns:
        the SubArea/Network list
        Throws:
        InterpssException
